7.7.7.1 Liens held by SVB, as per the SVB Loan Agreement (subject to the terms and conditions of any subordination agreement contemplated by Section 7.4 hereof), and Liens held by SFJ;

7.7.7.2 Liens for taxes, fees, assessments, or other government charges or levies that are being contested in good faith and for which PB does not have sufficient reserves on its books and records, provided that notice of such Lien has been filed or recorded under the IRC;

7.7.7.3 Purchase money Liens or capital leases (i) on equipment acquired or held by PB incurred for financing the acquisition of the equipment securing no more than [***] in the aggregate amount outstanding, or (ii) existing on equipment when acquired, if the Lien is confined to the property and improvements and the proceeds of the equipment, but with priority given to SFJ's security interest;

7.7.7.4 Leases or subleases of real property granted in the ordinary course of PB’s business (or, if referring to another Person, in the ordinary course of such Person’s business), and leases, subleases, non-exclusive licenses or sublicenses of personal property (other than Intellectual Property) granted in the ordinary course of PB’s business (or, if referring to another Person, in the ordinary course of such Person’s business), if the leases, subleases, licenses and sublicenses permit SFJ to obtain a security interest therein;

7.7.7.5 Interests of lessors and licensors under leases and licenses to PB of real property and personal property, but SFJ's interest has precedence;

7.7.7.6 The Existing Licenses, unless specifically granted to SFJ;

7.7.7.7 Excluded Licensing Transactions, except for those explicitly granted to SFJ;

7.7.7.8 Liens of carriers, warehousemen, suppliers, or other Persons that are possessory in nature arising in the ordinary course of business so long as such Liens attach only to inventory, securing liabilities in the aggregate amount which are delinquent or have become payable with penalties;

7.7.7.9 Liens to secure payment of workers’ compensation, employment insurance, old-age pensions, social security and other like obligations incurred in the ordinary course of business (other than Liens imposed by ERISA) that have not been contested in good faith or by appropriate proceedings;

7.7.7.10 Liens arising from attachments or judgments, orders, or decrees occurring after the Effective Date in circumstances constituting a Fundamental Breach by PB;

7.7.7.11 Liens in favor of financial institutions arising in connection with PB’s deposit and/or securities accounts held at such institutions, except for cases where SFJ has a first priority perfected security interest in the amounts held in such deposit and/or securities accounts;

7.7.7.12 Liens incurred in the extension, renewal or refinancing of the indebtedness secured by Liens described in Sections 7.7.7.1 through 7.7.7.11 (excluding Liens securing the SVB Loan, solely to the extent of any obligations thereunder permitted in accordance with the terms and conditions of the subordination agreement contemplated by Section 7.4 hereof), but any extension, renewal or replacement Lien must exceed the property encumbered by the existing Lien and may increase the principal amount of the indebtedness;

7.7.7.13 Deposits securing bids or contracts, unless specifically held by SFJ;

7.7.7.14 Liens securing the payment of purchase obligations for equipment, materials and inventory and for the payment of equipment and real estate lease obligations (including security deposits in connection therewith), except when held by SFJ;

7.7.7.15 Other Liens securing liabilities in an aggregate amount exceeding [***].
